<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="312" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[2732,3535,1250,1819]" lastBlockId="33.[1907,3532,1832,3455]" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[2735,3152,1409,1448]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shortridgei">
<emphasis box="[2735,3152,1409,1448]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">Rhinolophus shortridgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in the 
<emphasis box="[2732,2871,1462,1501]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">pusiUus</emphasis>
species group; it is close to 
<emphasis box="[3396,3534,1462,1501]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">
R 
<emphasis box="[2737,2852,1515,1554]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">monticolus,</emphasis>
</emphasis>
and together these two make 
<emphasis box="[3425,3534,1515,1554]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">
R 
<emphasis box="[2735,2825,1567,1606]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">pusiUus</emphasis>
</emphasis>
paraphyletic. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[3115,3534,1567,1606]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shortridgei">
<emphasis box="[3115,3534,1567,1606]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">Rhinolophus shortridgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<emphasis box="[2815,3007,1621,1660]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">previously</emphasis>
included in 
<emphasis box="[3264,3532,1621,1660]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1844" box="[3264,3443,1621,1660]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepidus">R lepidus</taxonomicName>
, but
</emphasis>
is recognized as a distinct species based on morphological and genetic differences presented 
<emphasis box="[2936,2980,1780,1819]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">by</emphasis>
G. Csorba and colleagues in 2003 and by P. Soisook and others in 2016. The precise distribution of this species has not been well established in the areas where it comes together with 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1844" box="[3235,3414,1885,1924]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="312" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepidus">R lepidus</taxonomicName>
, especially
</emphasis>
as the two are sympatric in some areas. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
